overview: The user initiated the project by providing a Statement of Work for a
  sleep questionnaire application, seeking to integrate a database for response
  storage, an admin dashboard for data access, and an authentication system. The
  approach involved updating the application's demographic data structure to
  align with the SOW, defining a new  model in Prisma for
  PostgreSQL (NeonDB), and creating RESTful API endpoints for saving,
  retrieving, and exporting questionnaire data as CSV. A key decision was to
  implement a simple password-based authentication system for the admin
  dashboard. Initially, a custom session management was set up, but it was later
  refined to leverage Next.js middleware for more streamlined route protection
  and a simpler cookie-based session. The outcome is a fully functional system
  where questionnaire responses are stored, accessible via a protected admin
  dashboard, and exportable as CSV, meeting all the SOW requirements.
